{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_brookland_ver01/data/sn84026749/00222254632/1930082201/0540.xml":{"full_text":"16\nI 1\nIpSEh\ni I'\u25a0 c __ i 4 f 1\nMarket Action Points Higher, With Chance of Recovery, Avers Spectator\nWEEK-END PROFIT liKIIG\nTO SLOW EXCIUIKE\nSteadily Rising Markets Should Not Be Ex\npected; Series of Trading Markets\nExpected for Some Time\nBy THE SPECTATOR\nThe market by its action is pointing higher. There was\nlittle sell-off yesterday, with a rally at the close.\nThe advance is likely to be resumed today on the encourag\nIng news that brokers loans were down for the week. On the\nother hand, there will probably be considerable profit-taking\non the approach of the week-end. which may bring about a\nstand-off.\nDon't expect any steadily rising markets for a while, not\nc at least until the business picture looks healthier. The best\nthat can be looked for is a series of trading markets, with\nwide swings in individual issues. I believe, however, that the\ndanger of a serious reaction is over for a while, and that there\nis much less risk in buying |he leading stocks than a month\nago.\nThe big fellows feel friendlier to the market. Buying has\nbeen bettei than the selling for the past week. The market\nhas strong sponsorship. My advice yesterday* was to buy the\ngood stocks on reactions. This advice still holds good.\nA Good Sign\nBrokers* loans were down $27,-\n000,000 last week to $3,128,000,000,\nthe lowest level in three years.\nThis occurred while the market\nwas forging steadily ahead, a\nhealthy sign. It would indicate\nthat stocks were passing into\nstrong hands, which brightens\nthe immediate outlook for the\nmarket.\nLoans at this time last year\nwere $6,085,000,000. When the\nbig interests are ready to put\nreal cash into the market, it\nwould seem that the little fellow\ncan follow their example; at\nleast, until some warhing signal\nIs given. Reactions are not likely\ntb go far.\nThe oils are still staggering\nunder the blows of the passing\nof the Shell Union and Warner\nQuinlan dividends and the un\nsettled condition of the industry\nas a whole. They were soft yes\nterday on disgusted liquidation\nand scattered selling. I am bull\nish on the leading oils, but buyers\nmust remember that they may\nneed the patience of Job before\nany big market in the petroleum\nstocks develops.\nBusiness Machines\nJ An analysis of companies mak\ning business machines and office\nequipment being completed by\nq\u2019ne of the leading banks puts\nInternational Business Machines\nat the top of the heap. This\ncompany is said to be best situ\nated to get foreign business if\nahy tariff reprisals take place.\nEarnings have been good, despite\nthe business depression.\nRemington Rand is said to be\nless favorably situated, due to\nexpiration soon of typewriter\npatents in several countries\nabroad and the likelihood of in\ncreased competition. Underwood\nElliott is highly regarded in con\nservative quarters. National Cash\nRegister should do better.\nI consider Chesapeake and\nOhio one of the cheapest high\ngrade stocks on the big board.\nEaftiings for the first seven\nmonths were well over $2 a share,\nahd Chesapeake should earn at\nleast $4 on the common for the\nyear. The stock should go to 60\nIh any kind of a market on earn\nings alone. Any rise in C. and\nO. will be reflected in higher\nprices for Chesapeake Corporation\nand Allegheny.\nDangerous Game\nThe rails, Southern Railway in\nparticular, again were the target\nof, the bears yesterday. It looks\nto me as though shorts may be\nselling themselves into a bag on\nthe leading carriers. This seems\na rather late date to hammer\naway at the railroads because\ntheir earnings are bad. They\nshould be better rather than\nworse before long.\nSouthern, especially, is danger\nous on the short side. The stock\nhas a big short interest already,\nand a director was quoted only\ntwo days age as repeating that\nthe $8 dividend would be paid\nthis year. Earnings for 1930 are\nReal Estate\nLoans\n(D. C. Property Only)*\no%\nNo Commituon Char god\nYou can take 12 years to pay oft\nyour loan without the expense of\nrenewing. SI,OOO for $lO per\nmonth including interest and,\nprincipal. Larger or smaller\nJoans at proportionate rates.\nPERPETUAL\nBUILDING\nASSOCIATION\nEstablished 1881\nLargest in Washington\n.Asset* Over $23,000,000\n.Cor. Ilth IM) g N. W.\n*\u00bb\u00ae*RY. PwoMest\nEDWARD C. BALTZ. Semtary\nWASHINGTON TIMESsFINANCIAL NEWS\nestimated at only $4 on the com\nmon, it is true, but next year\nmay tell a different story, and is\na long way off.\nThere is a better feeling\naround about Woolworth. The\nstock has a good rating. August\nsales, I am told, will be lower,\nbut will make a better showing\nwith a year ago. There is some\ntalk of an increased dividend by\nthe end of the year if earnings\nshow a real comeback.\nHere and There\nThey are talking of 40 for U.\nO. 1., but interests close to the\ncompany say they know nothing\nof any coming move. Better\nearnings of Public Service of New\nJersey is bullish on U. G. I. and\nUnited Corporation. Both, have\nhuge blocks of Public Service.\nI hear smart people have been\nbuying lard and expect it to go\nto 15 cents. It was up 2 cents\nyesterday.\nA clever statistician lists five\nstocks he believes will be way up\nfront in the next bull market.\nThey are American and Foreign\nPower, Houston Oil, Case Thresh\ning, Worthington Pump, and\nUnited Aircraft. Pump is acting\nas though it were ready for some\nof its old \"whoopee\u201d on the up\nside.\nI hear there may be a quick\nplay in Raybestos Manhattan.\nThere is similar talk about U. S.\nPipe and Foundry.\nCotton is considered cheap for\na long pull. It may be a real\nlong one, though.\nI hear of good buying in Radio\nand Radio Keith. They are talk\ning of a big move in Radio. Some\nsay 70, but I would settle for less\nif I owned the stock. Radio\nKeith\u2019s earnings are. being revised\nupward.\n\u00b0K homes, eave time\n